03ca href=\"https://www.history.com/topics/world-war-ii/world-war-ii-history\"\u003eWorld War II\u003c/a\u003e by President \u003ca href=\"https://www.history.com/topics/us-presidents/franklin-d-roosevelt\"\u003eFranklin D. Roosevelt\u003c/a\u003e through his \u003ca href=\"https://www.archives.gov/historical-docs/todays-doc/?dod-date=219\"\u003eExecutive Order 9066\u003c/a\u003e. From 1942 to 1945, it was the policy of the U.S. government that people of Japanese descent, including U.S. citizens, would be incarcerated in isolated camps. Enacted in reaction to the \u003ca href=\"https://www.history.com/topics/world-war-ii/pearl-harbor\"\u003ePearl Harbor\u003c/a\u003e attacks and the ensuing war, the incarceration of Japanese Americans is considered one of the most atrocious violations of American civil rights in the 20th century.","dropCap":false},"innerBlocks":[]}]},{"clientId":"9d53611b-d063-4217-b685-db0a8aaa80b1","name":"history/video","attributes":{"platformId":"1064511043882","contentRating":"TV-PG","duration":0,"title":"Japanese-American Relocation","disableAutoplay":false,"description":"After the attack on Pearl Harbor, the United States Government issued executive order 9066, which empowered the military to round up anyone of Japanese ancestry and place them in internment camps.","pplId":["200170"],"restrictionId":0,"publicUrl":"https://link.theplatform.com/s/xc6n8B/media/gyob8D3BOMpC","rating":"TV-PG","poster":"https://cropper.watch.aetnd.com/public-content-aetn.video.aetnd.com/video-thumbnails/AETN-History_VMS/413/863/BRAND_SF_THC_HOSF_200170_SUP_2398_20170510_01_0513883_HD.jpg"},"innerBlocks":[]},{"clientId":"46fcf256-4bfe-44cc-ab89-00b45bd705bd","name":"core/heading","attributes":{"content":"Executive Order 9066","level":2,"id":"executive-order-9066"},"innerBlocks":[]},{"clientId":"f8e4e1e5-5c01-4ed3-ab05-6dc0b5e1daef","name":"core/paragraph","attributes":{"content":"On February 19, 1942, shortly after the bombing of \u003ca href=\"https://www.history.c